Members of the Welsh Assembly don't want to "look at the mappets"
Some members of the National Assembly are dissatisfied with the proposal to adopt the abbreviation MWP (Member of the Welsh Parliament) for their names.
The resolution is related to plans to change the name of the Assembly to the Parliament of Wales.
Members of the Assembly from different political parties are concerned about possible jokes with this abbreviation.
One Labour member, expressing his party's opinion, expressed concern that the new abbreviation "remnants Twp and Pwp".
For our readers, not from Wales: in Welsh twp means “stupid”, and pwp means “cuckoo”.
According to a member of the Assembly from the Welsh Party, his organization as a whole “remained dissatisfied” and offered other options.
Representatives of the conservative party “do not object” to the new abbreviation, but note that the MWP is close to writing the word Muppet (map).
In this context, the letter w in Welsh is pronounced roughly like the letter u in the Yorkshire English dialect.
The Assembly Committee, currently drafting the renaming bill, made the following statement: “The final decision on the names of the Members of the Assembly will, of course, remain with them.”
The Wales Governance Act of 2017 empowers the National Assembly of Wales to change its name.
In June, the Committee published the results of a public opinion poll on the proposed options, according to which the "Parliament of Wales" option instead of the "Assembly" found widespread support among the local population.
As for the names of the members of the Assembly, the Committee preferred the Welsh Parliament Members (WMP) option, while the MWP option received the most public support.
It seems that the members of the Assembly are proposing other options, but it will be difficult for the Chairman, Elin Jones, to find a solution that suits everyone. It should be recalled that the draft law on amendments should be submitted in a few weeks.
The reform laws would include other modifications to the Assembly ' s working process, including new rules on the disqualification of members of the Assembly and the structure of the Committee ' s system.
Members of the Assembly will vote on the final version of their name during the debate on the bill.
