The Labour Party is no longer an organization that holds different views.
She is not tolerant of those who speak her mind.
When Momentum activists in my local party put forward a motion of no confidence in me, it was no surprise.
I am, after all, the last of the Labour Party Members of Parliament who have not yet been told that we are not welcome for our opinion.
