The commissioning of a new German warship has been postponed again.
The newest frigate of the German fleet was supposed to be commissioned in 2014 to replace the aging Cold War war warships, but this will not happen any less next year due to faulty systems and avalanche-like cost growth, local media reported.
The commissioning of the Rhineland-Palatinate, the main ship of the completely new frigates of the Baden-W<0xC3><0xBC>rttemberg class, has now been postponed until the first half of 2019, the newspaper Die Zeit reports, citing a military representative.
