The 7000-tonne Rhineland-Palatinate is believed to be twice as heavy as similar class ships used by the Germans in World War II.
In addition to faulty equipment, the cost of the entire project, including team training, also becomes a problem.
It is said to have reached a staggering 3.1 billion euros ($3.6 billion) compared to the original 2.2 billion euros.
